It reads "I hope you've had a chance to relax Barack...but pack your bags and call the number below. It's time to start the real job." Signed simply, "JFK." When you call the number that's listed, JFK answers the phone. You ask him, "What do you mean, John?" JFK responds, "Barry, you're in luck. As it turns out, the real job is to relax and be a great dad to Sasha and Malia." You respond, "John, of course I am enjoying retirement. So what are you talking about?"

JFK sighs into the phone. "Look, Barry, I've been watching you over the years. I saw how stressed out you were during your presidency and quite frankly, I'm worried about you. If you keep going at the stress rates you're going at, you might have a stroke or something, and I just don't want that on my conscience. So it's time for you to take a break and stop worrying about the country. And I need you to take a REAL break. Do you think you can do that?"

It reads "I hope you've had a chance to relax Barack...but pack your bags and call the number below. It's time to start the real job." Signed simply, "JFK." When you call the number that's listed, JFK answers the phone. You ask him, "What do you mean, John?" JFK responds, "Barry, you're in luck. As it turns out, the real job is to relax and be a great dad to Sasha and Malia." You respond, "John, of course I am enjoying retirement. So what are you talking about?"

JFK sighs into the phone. "Look, Barry, I've been watching you over the years. I saw how stressed out you were during your presidency and quite frankly, I'm worried about you. If you keep going at the stress rates you're going at, you might have a stroke or something, and I just don't want that on my conscience. So it's time for you to take a break and stop worrying about the country. And I need you to take a REAL break. Do you think you can do that?"
